FBIS4-66066 "drweu103_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Foreign Minister Responds Foreign Minister Responds LD2605163494 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1500 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605163494 Rome RAI Due Television Network Italian BFN [Excerpt] Italian Foreign Minister Antonio Martino who is currently in Paris attending the Conference on European Stability, has called the remarks of French President Francois Mitterrand unacceptable. Mitterrand, referring to the new Italian Government and the figure of Silvio Berlusconi, spoke of a fearful inroad on democracy. Martino said that these remarks were isolated and were the only ones uttered by a head of state. [passage omitted]
